<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 1420/98 of 26 June 1998 amending Regulation (EEC) No 619/71 laying down general rules for granting aid for flax and hemp </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1420/98, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 619/71, milles s&auml;testatakse abi andmise eeskirjad lina ja kanepi puhul 26. juuni 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1308/70 of 29 June 1970 on the common organisation of the market in flax and hemp (1), and in particular Article 4(4) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. juuni 1970. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1308/70 lina- ja kanepituru &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) eriti selle artikli 4 l&otilde;iget 4, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the second subparagraph of Article 4(1) or Regulation (EEC) No 1308/70 stipulates that aid is granted only for hemp grown from seed of varieties providing certain safeguards to be determined in respect of the content of intoxicating substances in the harvested product; whereas Article 3(1) of Regulation (EEC) No 619/71 (2) lays down a maximum limit for the average content of tetrahydrocannabinol (THC) to determine the varieties of seeds which may be accepted; whereas in order to strengthen the measures ensuring that land eligible for production aid may not be used for illegal cultivation the maximum limit currently laid down should be reduced; whereas, for the same purpose, the grant of aid should be made conditional upon harvesting after seed formation; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestadas, et: m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1308/70 artikli 4 l&otilde;ike 1 teises l&otilde;igus s&auml;testatakse, et abi antakse &uuml;ksnes kanepi jaoks, mis on kasvatatud selliste sortide seemnetest, mille puhul koristatud saagi joovastavate ainete sisalduse suhtes esitatakse teatavad tagatised; m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 619/71 (2) artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatakse tetrah&uuml;drokannabinooli (THK) lubatud keskmine sisaldus, et teha kindlaks lubatud seemnesordid; tootmistoetuse saamise tingimustele vastava maa-ala ebaseadusliku harimise v&auml;ltimiseks v&otilde;etavate meetmete tugevdamiseks tuleks v&auml;hendada praegu kehtivat lubatud maksimumpiiri; samal p&otilde;hjusel tuleks abi andmise tingimuseks seada saagi koristamine p&auml;rast seemnete moodustumist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 3(2) of Regulation (EEC) No 619/71 lays down, for the grant of aid for fibre flax, a system of compulsory contracts between producers and primary processors containing a processing undertaking; whereas a similar system of compulsory contracts should be introduced in the hemp sector so as to improve control of the final use of the crop and to guarantee that the crop is actually processed; whereas provision should also be made for the case where the producer processes the hemp into straw or has it processed on this behalf by a processor; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 619/71 artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatakse abi andmiseks kiulina jaoks tootjate ja esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejate vahel s&otilde;lmitavate t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise kohustust sisaldavate kohustuslike lepingute s&uuml;steem; samasugune kohustuslik lepingus&uuml;steem tuleks kehtestada kanepisektoris, et t&otilde;hustada saagi l&otilde;ppkasutuse kontrollimist ja tagada saagi tegelik t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine; s&auml;testada tuleks ka v&otilde;imalus, et tootja t&ouml;&ouml;tleb kanepi varteks v&otilde;i laseb seda teha enda nimel t&ouml;&ouml;tlejal; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 4 of Regulation (EEC) No 619/71 provides for a system of administrative supervision guaranteeing that the product of which aid has been requested qualifies for that aid; whereas provision should be made for the possibility of strengthening that supervision system in the hemp sector by a system of prior authorisation for sowing; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 619/71 artikliga 4 n&auml;hakse ette haldusj&auml;relevalve s&uuml;steem, millega tagatakse, et toode, mille jaoks abi taotletakse, vastab k&otilde;nealuse abi saamise tingimustele; s&auml;testada tuleks v&otilde;imalus nimetatud j&auml;relevalves&uuml;steemi tugevdamiseks kanepisektoris k&uuml;lvi eelloa andmise s&uuml;steemi abil; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation must be implemented under the best possible conditions; whereas, therefore, transitional measures may be needed to facilitate the changeover to the new system, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses etten&auml;htud meetmed tuleb rakendada v&otilde;imalikult soodsates tingimustes; seep&auml;rast v&otilde;ib uuele s&uuml;steemile &uuml;lemineku h&otilde;lbustamiseks vaja minna &uuml;leminekumeetmeid, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Regulation (EEC) No 619/71 is hereby amended as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 619/71 muudetakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3(1) shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 3 l&otilde;ige 1 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> '1. </inglise>
<eesti> "1. </eesti>
<inglise> For hemp, aid shall be granted only to growers, who have concluded, before a date to be specified, a contract with a primary processor approved by the competent authority in the Member State on whose territory his establishments are situated, under which the primary processor obtains ownership of the hemp and undertakes to process it. </inglise>
<eesti> Kanepi jaoks antakse abi &uuml;ksnes kasvatajatele, kes on enne t&auml;psustatavat kuup&auml;eva s&otilde;lminud lepingu esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejaga, kelle on heaks kiitnud selle liikmesriigi p&auml;dev asutus, mille territooriumil asuvad tema ettev&otilde;tted; lepingu alusel saab t&ouml;&ouml;tleja kanepi omanikuks ja kohustub seda t&ouml;&ouml;tlema. </eesti>
<inglise> However, aid shall also be granted to the producer if he undertakes to process the hemp into straw and is approved for that purpose by the competent authority or if he undertakes to have the hemp processed on his behalf into straw by an approved primary processor. </inglise>
<eesti> Siiski antakse abi ka tootjale, juhul kui ta kohustub t&ouml;&ouml;tlema kanepi ise varteks ja kui p&auml;dev asutus on tema selleks heaks kiitnud v&otilde;i juhul, kui ta laseb enda nimel kanepi varteks t&ouml;&ouml;delda heaks kiidetud esmat&ouml;&ouml;tlejal. </eesti>
<inglise> Aid shall be granted only for hemp harvested after seed formation and grown from certified seed of varieties contained in a list to be drawn up in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 12 of Regulation (EEC) No 1308/70. </inglise>
<eesti> Abi antakse &uuml;ksnes kanepi jaoks, mis on koristatud p&auml;rast seemnete moodustumist ja mis on kasvatatud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1308/70 artiklis 12 s&auml;testatud korras koostatavas loetelus esitatud sortide sertifitseeritud seemnest. </eesti>
<inglise> This list shall include only varieties for which a Member State has found by analysis that the weight of THC (tetrahydrocannabinol) in the weight of a sample maintained at constant weight is no more than: </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealune loetelu sisaldab &uuml;ksnes sorte, mille puhul on liikmesriik anal&uuml;&uuml;si teel leidnud, et p&uuml;simassiga proovi tetrah&uuml;drokannabinooli mass ei ole suurem kui: </eesti>
<inglise> - 0,3 % for the purposes of the grant of aid for the marketing years 1998/99 to 2000/2001, </inglise>
<eesti> - 0,3% abi andmise puhul turustusaastateks 1998/99 kuni 2000/2001, </eesti>
<inglise> - 0,2 % for the purposes of the grant of aid for subsequent marketing. </inglise>
<eesti> - 0,2% abi andmise puhul j&auml;rgmisteks turustusaastateks. </eesti>
<inglise> The sample referred to above shall consist of the upper third of a representative number of plants selected at random at the end of their flowering period and with stalks and seeds removed. </inglise>
<eesti> Eespool osutatud proov koosneb &otilde;itsemisaja l&otilde;pus juhuslikult valitud representatiivse hulga taimede &uuml;lemistest kolmandikest, millelt on eemaldatud varred ja seemned." </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In Article 4(1), the following subparagraph shall be added: </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 4 l&otilde;ikele 1 lisatakse j&auml;rgmine l&otilde;ik: </eesti>
<inglise> 'For hemp, if the Member State considers it appropriate, the arrangements shall comprise a system for the prior authorisation of sowing on land eligible for production aid. </inglise>
<eesti> "Juhul kui liikmesriik peab seda vajalikuks, v&otilde;ivad kanepi puhul meetmed h&otilde;lmata tootmistoetuse saamise tingimustele vastavale maa-alale k&uuml;lvamise eelloa andmise s&uuml;steemi." </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6a shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6a asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> 'Article 6a </inglise>
<eesti> "Artikkel 6a </eesti>
<inglise> Should transitional measures be strictly necessary to facilitate the implementation of the adjustments to the arrangements laid down in Regulation (EC) No 1420/98 (*) with effect from the 1998/99 marketing year, such measures shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 12 of Regulation (EEC) No 1308/70. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui &uuml;leminekumeetmed on v&auml;ltimatud, h&otilde;lbustamaks m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 1420/98* s&auml;testatud korra kohanduste rakendamiseks alates 1998/99. turustusaastast, v&otilde;etakse sellised meetmed m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1308/70 artiklis 12 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall apply until the end of the 1999/2000 marketing year at the latest. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealuseid meetmeid kohaldatakse k&otilde;ige kauem kuni 1999/2000. turustusaasta l&otilde;puni. </eesti>
<inglise> (*) OJ L 190, 4.7.1998, p. 7. </inglise>
<eesti> * E&Uuml;T L 190, 4.07.1998, lk 7." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from the 1998/99 marketing year. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse alates 1998/99. turustusaastast. </eesti>
<inglise> However, Article 1(3) shall apply from the date of the entry into force of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Artikli 1 l&otilde;iget 3 kohaldatakse siiski alates k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumise kuup&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Luxembourg, 26 June 1998. </inglise>
